n-17eme-cas-confirme-hanoi-275441|title=COVID-19 au Vietnam : un 17\u00e8me cas confirm\u00e9 \u00e0 Hanoi|website=lepetitjournal.com|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Europe===\n\n'''Albania''' \u2013\nOn 9 March, a 54-year-old man and his 28-year-old son, who had travelled from Florence to Albania by car, were confirmed positive.<ref>{{cite news |title=Konfirmohen dy rastet e para me koronavirusin e ri |url=http://shendetesia.gov.al/ministria-e-shendetesise-konfirmohen-dy-rastet-e-para-me-koronavirusin-e-ri/ |accessdate=9 March 2020 |date=9 March 2020 |language=Albanian}}</ref> Three other people from the men's family were suspected of having the virus. Another Albanian who had gone to Italy for a one-day trip is suspected.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Andorra''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, Andorra registered its first case, a 20-year-old man who had been to Milan.<ref>{{cite news |title=Andorra registra su primer caso de coronavirus |url=https://www.diarimes.com/es/noticias/actualidad/2020/03/02/andorra_registra_primer_caso_coronavirus_77612_1095.html |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=DiariMes.com |date=2 March 2020 |language=es}}</ref>\n\n'''Austria''' \u2013\nOn 25 February, Austria confirmed its first two cases, a 24-year-old man and a 24-year-old woman from Lombardy who had visited their hometown in Bergamo, tested positive and were treated at a hospital in [[Innsbruck]], [[Tyrol (state)|Tyrol]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://orf.at/stories/3155602/|title=Coronavirus: Zwei F\u00e4lle in Tirol best\u00e4tigt|last=red|first=ORF at/Agenturen|date=25 February 2020|website=news.ORF.at|language=de|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Busby (now)|first=Mattha|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2020/feb/25/coronavirus-live-updates-outbreak-latest-news-italy-italia-deaths-symptoms-china-stocks-wall-street-dow-jones-economy-falls?page=with%3Ablock-5e550d8a8f086a28115b222d|title=Coronavirus news: Austria and Croatia report first cases as Tenerife quarantines hotel \u2013 live updates|date=25 February 2020|work=The Guardian|access-date=25 February 2020|last2=Belam|first2=Martin|issn=0261-3077|last3=Marsh|first3=Sarah|last4=Rourke|first4=Alison|last5=Farrer (earlier)|first5=Martin|last6=Busby|first6=Mattha|last7=Adams|first7=Richard|last8=Parveen|first8=Nazia|last9=Wearden|first9=Graeme}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-25-20-hnk-intl/h_66850dfa7d9602fb4b0d38efdd19d939|title=Austria's 2 coronavirus cases are Italian citizens|first1=Helen |last1=Regan |first2=Adam |last2=Renton |first3=Meg |last3=Wagner |first4=Mike |last4=Hayes |first5=Veronica|last5=Rocha|date=25 February 2020|publisher=CNN|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-austria-idUSKBN20J1OJ|title=Austria seals off Innsbruck hotel after reporting first two coronavirus cases|date=25 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 27 February, a couple who tested positive and their two children who were showing symptoms were admitted to Kaiser-Franz-Josef Hospital. The family was previously on holiday in Lombardy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wien.orf.at/stories/3036506/|title=Coronavirus: Drei best\u00e4tigte F\u00e4lle in Wien|last=red|first=wien ORF at/Agenturen|date=27 February 2020|website=wien.ORF.at|language=de|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.derstandard.at/jetzt/livebericht/2000115088241/coronaviruserster-bestaetigter-fall-in-wien|title=Dritter best\u00e4tigter Coronavirus-Fall in Wien \u2013 derStandard.at|website=DER STANDARD|language=de-AT|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> On 28 February, one of the children, a 15-year-old boy, tested positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://orf.at/stories/3156035/|title=Infektion in Steiermark: Bereits sieben best\u00e4tigte CoV-F\u00e4lle|last=red|first=ORF at/Agenturen|date=28 February 2020|website=news.ORF.at|language=de|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Belgium''' \u2013\nNine patients diagnosed with the virus had travelled from Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.info-coronavirus.be/fr/2020/03/04/10-nouveaux-patients-contamines-par-le-covid-19-dans-notre-pays-sur-495-tests/|title=Coronavirus COVID-19|website=info-coronavirus.be|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> Belgium has confirmed that there are many more and that Italy is the source of most of its cases.\n\n'''Belarus''' \u2013\nA case was confirmed as having been imported from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://belsat.eu/en/news/six-coronavirus-cases-in-belarus-ministry/|title=Six coronavirus cases in Belarus \u2013 ministry|website=belsat.eu|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aysor.am/en/news/2020/03/04/belarus-coronavirus/1666615|title=Six coronavirus cases confirmed in Belarus \u2013 aysor.am \u2013 Hot news from Armenia|first=Helix Consulting|last=LLC|website=aysor.am|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Bosnia and Herzegovina''' \u2013\nA man working in Italy transmitted the virus to his child.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://balkaninsight.com/2020/03/05/bosnia-confirms-two-coronavirus-cases-expects-more/|title=Bosnia Confirms Two Coronavirus Cases, Expects More|date=5 March 2020|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Croatia''' \u2013\nOn 25 February, Croatia confirmed its first case, a 26-year-old man who had stayed in Milan between 19 and 21 February and was hospitalised at the Dr. Fran Mihaljevi\u0107 University Hospital for Infectious Diseases in [[Zagreb]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Newey|first=Sarah|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/global-health/science-and-disease/coronavirus-news-uk-italy-china-south-korea-pandemic/|title=Coronavirus latest news: Britons returning from Italy told to self-isolate as Matt Hancock says he is 'worried'|date=25 February 2020|work=The Telegraph|access-date=25 February 2020|last2=Kelly-Linden|first2=Jordan|issn=0307-1235|last3=Team|first3=Global Health S