5.html|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a4\u03ad\u03c4\u03b1\u03c1\u03c4\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u2013 \u039a\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03b3\u03ae\u03c4\u03c1\u03b9\u03b1 36 \u03b5\u03c4\u03ce\u03bd \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0391\u03b8\u03ae\u03bd\u03b1|date=28 February 2020|work=News247|access-date=28 February 2020|language=el |trans-title=Coronavirus: Fourth Case \u2013 36-year-old Professor in Athens }}</ref>\n\n'''Hungary''' \u2013\nThree of the seven cases in Hungary reported to date are linked to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://koronavirus.gov.hu/cikkek/hetre-nott-koronavirus-fertozottek-szama-tegnap-esti-eredmenyek-szerint|title=H\u00e9tre n\u0151tt a koronav\u00edrus-fert\u0151z\u00f6ttek sz\u00e1ma a tegnap esti eredm\u00e9nyek szerint|language=hu|date=7 March 2020|accessdate=8 March 2020|via=koronavirus.gov.hu}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://koronavirus.gov.hu/cikkek/diagnosztizaltak-az-otodik-koronavirus-fertozottet-idos-magyar-beteg-ferfi|title=Diagnosztiz\u00e1lt\u00e1k az \u00f6t\u00f6dik koronav\u00edrus-fert\u0151z\u00f6ttet \u2013 id\u0151s, magyar, beteg f\u00e9rfi|date=7 March 2020|language=hu|accessdate=8 March 2020|via=koronavirus.gov.hu}}</ref>\n\n'''Iceland''' \u2013\nOn 28 February 2020, Iceland confirmed its first case, an Icelandic male in his 50s who had previously been to Northern Italy and was placed in strict [[Isolation (health care)|isolation]] in [[Landsp\u00edtali]] in [[Reykjav\u00edk]].<ref name=\"ruv.is\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ruv.is/frett/fyrsta-tilfelli-covid-19-greint-a-islandi|title=Fyrsta tilfelli COVID-19 greint \u00e1 \u00cdslandi|date=28 February 2020|website=R\u00daV}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bnonews.com/index.php/2020/02/the-latest-coronavirus-cases/|title=Tracking coronavirus: Map, data and timeline|first=B. N. O.|last=News|date=18 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mbl.is/frettir/innlent/2020/02/28/fyrsta_tilfelli_koronuveiru_greinist_a_islandi/|title=Fyrsta tilfelli k\u00f3r\u00f3nuveiru greinist \u00e1 \u00cdslandi|website=mbl.is|language=is|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 5 March, a total of 34 cases had been confirmed in Iceland, most of which are imported cases from Italy.\n\n'''Ireland''' \u2013\nOn 27 February 2020, Ireland's first case was confirmed by the [[Health Protection Surveillance Centre]]. The male patient had travelled to an affected region in Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/coronavirus/2020/0229/1119357-coronavirus-ireland/ |title=First case of Covid-19 diagnosed in east of Ireland |date=1 March 2020 |access-date=4 March 2020 |publisher=Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann }}</ref> A second, unrelated case was confirmed on 3 March, a female in the eastern portion of Ireland who had travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|first1=Paul|last1=Cullen|accessdate=3 March 2020|title=Second case of coronavirus is confirmed in east of Ireland|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/health/second-case-of-coronavirus-is-confirmed-in-east-of-ireland-1.4191961|website=The Irish Times}}</ref>\n\n'''Latvia''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, Latvia confirmed its first case, a person who had travelled from Milan to Munich and then to [[Riga]] on 29 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eng.lsm.lv/article/society/health/first-case-of-covid-19-coronavirus-confirmed-in-latvia.a350338/|title=First case of COVID-19 coronavirus confirmed in Latvia|website=lsm.lv|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Lithuania''' \u2013\nOn 28 February, Lithuania confirmed its first case, a 39-year-old woman who arrived in [[Kaunas]] from [[Verona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.15min.lt/naujiena/aktualu/lietuva/koronavirusas-pasieke-lietuva-uzfiksuotas-pirmasis-atvejis-56-1282110|title=Lietuvoje patvirtintas pirmasis koronaviruso atvejis \u2013 susirgo 39 met\u0173 moteris, atskridusi \u012f Kaun\u0105|website=15min.lt|language=lt|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Luxembourg''' \u2013\nThe nation's second and fourth cases were persons who had travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://5minutes.rtl.lu/actu/luxembourg/a/1479054.html|title=RTL 5minutes \u2013 Il revenait d'Italie: Un deuxi\u00e8me cas de coronavirus confirm\u00e9 au Luxembourg|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://5minutes.rtl.lu/actu/luxembourg/a/1479918.html|title=Sant\u00e9: Un 4e cas de coronavirus valid\u00e9 au Luxembourg|website=5minutes.rtl.lu|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Malta''' \u2013\nA 12-year-old Italian brought the infection to Malta.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/covid19-malta-first-coronavirus-case-italian-girl-12512852|title=Italian girl becomes Malta's first coronavirus case|website=CNA|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Moldova''' \u2013\nOn 7 March, Moldova confirmed its first case, a 48-year-old woman who had returned from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deschide.md/ro/stiri/social/62248/BREAKING-NEWS-Primul-caz-de-coronavirus-depistat-%C3%AEn-Republica-Moldova-O-femeie-de-48-de-ani-infectat%C4%83.htm|title=BREAKING NEWS// Primul caz de coronavirus depistat \u00een Republica Moldova. O femeie de 48 de ani, infectat\u0103|trans-title=BREAKING NEWS// First coronavirus case detected in Republic of Moldova. A 48-year-old woman, infected|language=ro|website=Deschide.md|date=7 March 2020|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref> Moldova confirmed the existence of imported case from diseased Italy on 11 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://stiri.md/article/incidente/al-patrulea-caz-de-coronavirus-confirmat-in-r-moldova|title=Al patrulea caz de coronavirus, confirmat \u00een R. Moldova|website=stiri.md|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Netherlands''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, the Netherlands confirmed its first case, a man who had been in Lombardy and was admitted to Elisabeth-TweeSteden Hospital in [[Tilburg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rivm.nl/nieuws/patient-met-nieuw-coronavirus-in-nederland|title=Pati\u00ebnt met nieuw coronavirus in Nederland {{!}} RIVM|website=www.rivm.nl|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraaf.nl/nieuws/214089776/rivm-eerste-coronageval-in-nederland|title=RIVM: eerste coronageval in Nederland|date=27 February 2020|website=De Telegraaf|language=nl|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a woman from [[Amsterdam]] who had visited Lombardy was in home isolation in [[Diemen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rivm.nl/nieuws/tweede-patient-in-nederland-met-covid-19|title=Tweede pati\u00ebnt in Nederland met COVID-19 {{!}} RIVM|website=www.rivm.nl|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[North Macedonia]]''' \u2013\nOn 26 February, North Macedonia confirmed its first case, a woman who tested positive at the Clinic for Infectious Diseases, [[Skopje]]. She had stayed in Italy for a month and had been sick for two weeks. Upon returning to North Macedonia, she immediately reported to the clinic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vesti.mk/read/article/https%3A%2F%2Freporter.mk%2Fgjuture%2Fpotvrden-prv-sluchaj-od-koronavirus-vo-makedonija%2F|title=\u041f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d \u043f\u0440\u0432 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 |trans-title=First confirmed case of coronavirus in Macedonia |date=n.d.|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|language=Macedonian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://a1on.mk/macedonia/prv-sluchaj-na-zabolen-od-koronavirus-vo-makedonija/|title=\u041f\u0440\u0432 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|date=26 February 2020|website=\u04101\u043e\u043d|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Norway''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, Norway confirmed that two people who tested positive were linked to the outbreak in Italy. They were quarantined at home in [[Oslo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fhi.no/nyheter/2020/tre-nye-personer-har-testet-positivt-pa-koronavirus/|title=Tre nye personer har testet positivt p\u00e5 koronavirus|website=Folkehelseinstituttet|language=no|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, an individual from Bergen and an employee of [[Oslo University Hospital, Ullev\u00e5l]] tested positive and were placed in home isolation. Both had visited Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nrk.no/vestland/over-hundre-kan-ha-hatt-kontakt-med-koronasmittet-ulleval-ansatt-1.14922358|title=Over hundre kan ha hatt kontakt med koronasmittet Ullev\u00e5l-ansatt|last=Olsson|first=Svein Vestrum|date=28 February 2020|publisher=NRK|language=nb-NO|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fhi.no/nyheter/2020/ytterligere-to-personer-har-testet-positivt-pa-koronavirus/|title=Ytterligere to personer har testet positivt p\u00e5 koronavirus|website=Folkehelseinstituttet|language=no|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 6 March, the Norwegian Institute of Public Health reported that 79 of the 113 confirmed cases in Norway were linked to the outbreak in northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fhi.no/en/news/2020/status-coronavirus-friday-6.-mars-2020/|title=Status coronavirus Friday 6. mars 2020|website=Folkehelseinstituttet|date=6 March 2020|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Poland''' \u2013\nOf the country's first five cases, two were from Italy, two were from Germany and one was from the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://polandin.com/47007012/four-new-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-in-poland|title=Four new coronavirus cases confirmed in Poland|first=Telewizja Polska|last=S.A|website=polandin.com|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Portugal''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, a doctor who had travelled to Northern Italy and became ill on 29 February was confirmed positive at Hospital de S\u00e3o Jo\u00e3o in [[Porto]]. On 4 March, a 44-year-old man who had travelled to Italy was confirmed positive at the same hospital.\n\n'''Romania''' \u2013\nOn 26 February, Romania confirmed its first case, a man from [[Gorj County|Gorj]] who tested positive after having come in contact with an 71-year-old man from [[Cattolica]], Italy. The Italian man visited his wife's family and had several business meetings in Romania from 18 to 22 February. The Romanian man was admitted to National Institute of Infectious Diseases Prof. Dr. Matei Bal\u0219 in [[Bucharest]].<ref name=\":5\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-sanatate-23687251-primul-caz-infectie-coronavirus-confirmat-oficial-romania.htm|title=ULTIMA OR\u0102 LIVEVIDEOTEXT Primul caz de infec\u021bie cu coronavirus, confirmat oficial \u00een Rom\u00e2nia: Un b\u0103rbat din Gorj care a intrat \u00een contact cu italianul care a vizitat recent \u021bara noastr\u0103 \u2013 Sanatate \u2013 HotNews.ro|date=26 February 2020|website=hotnews.ro|language=ro|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a 45-year-old man from [[Maramure\u0219]] who had returned from Italy on 25 February was admitted to the Clinic of Infectious Diseases and then transferred to [[Cluj County|Cluj]].<ref name=\":9\">{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/doua-noi-posibile-cazuri-de-coronavirus-in-romania-1267704|title=Dou\u0103 noi cazuri de coronavirus confirmate \u00een Rom\u00e2nia|website=digi24.ro|language=ro|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> A 38-year-old woman who had returned from Bergamo tested positive was admitted to a hospital in [[Timi\u0219oara]].<ref name=\":9\" />\nOn 3 March, a 47-year-old man who had travelled in the same plane with the 38-year-old woman was confirmed positive and admitted to the same hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/al-patrulea-caz-de-coronavirus-confirmat-in-romania-1269577|title=Al patrulea caz de coronavirus a fost confirmat \u00een Rom\u00e2nia|trans-title=Fourth coronavirus case was confirmed in Romania|language=ro|website=Digi24|date=3 March 2020|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\nThe majority of confirmed cases in Romania are related to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/informatii-oficiale-despre-coronavirus-ministerul-de-interne-26-de-persoane-sunt-in-carantina-2077-sunt-monitorizate-la-domiciliu-1266261|title=Coronavirus Rom\u00e2nia, INFORMA\u021aII OFICIALE: 36 de persoane au fost infectate. Primul medic confirmat cu COVID-19|trans-title=Coronavirus Romania, OFFICIAL INFORMATION: 36 people got infected. First medic infected with COVID-19|language=ro|website=Digi24|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|date=11 March 2020|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Russia''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, a Russian citizen who had returned from Italy was diagnosed.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian citizen who returned from Italy diagnosed with coronavirus: RIA cites ministry |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-russia/russian-citizen-who-returned-from-italy-diagnosed-with-coronavirus-ria-cites-ministry-idUSKBN20P1JH |accessdate=4 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |date=2 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\n'''San Marino''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, San Marino confirmed its first case, an 88-year-old man with pre-existing medical conditions who was hospitalised at Rimini Hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.altarimini.it/News132152-coronavirus-primo-caso-nella-repubblica-di-san-marino.php|title=Coronavirus: primo caso nella Repubblica di San Marino|date=27 February 2020|website=Altarimini.it|language=it|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.libertas.sm/notizie/2020/02/27/coronavirus-primo-caso-a-san-marino-attivati-i-protocolli-sanitari.html|title=Coronavirus: primo caso a San Marino. Attivati i protocolli sanitari.|last=webit.it|last2=Libertas|website=Libertas|language=it|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Serbia''' \u2013\nOn 6 March, Serbia registered its first case, a 43-year-old man who had been to Budapest and Italy. At least one other case had been to Italy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/serbian/lat/srbija-51831539|title=Korona virus: Potvr\u0111eno \u0161est novih slu\u010dajeva u Srbiji|newspaper=BBC News Na Srpskom|date=11 March 2020|accessdate=12 March 2020|via=bbc.com}}</ref>\n\n'''Slovakia''' \u2013\nAn asymptomatic man who had travelled to Venice between 14 and 15 February transmitted the virus to his father and his wife.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://spectator.sme.sk/c/22352401/three-coronavirus-cases-in-slovakia.html|title=Three coronavirus cases confirmed in Slovakia|first=Petit Press|last=a.s|date=7 March 2020|website=spectator.sme.sk|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Slovenia''' \u2013\nMany Slovenian cases are linked to Italy, including the nation's first case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.24ur.com/novice/slovenija/epidemiologi-iscejo-vse-s-katerimi-je-imel-okuzeni-slovenec-stike.html|title=Oku\u017ebo s koronavirusom potrdili \u017ee pri \u0161estih osebah, ne gre samo za motoriste iz Maroka|website=24ur.com|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Spain''' \u2013\nOn 24 February, a 69-year-old medical doctor from Lombardy who had been vacationing in [[Tenerife]] since 17 February tested positive at the [[Hospital Universitario Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Candelaria|University Hospital of the Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Candelaria]]. A 25-year-old man returning from a holiday in Italy also tested positive in [[Asturias]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_italiano_positivo_al_test_a_tenerife_e_il_terzo_caso_di_contagio_in_spagna-249508945/|title=Turista italiano positivo al test a Tenerife. Primo caso sospetto nelle Asturie: \u00e8 un giovane di ritorno dall'Italia|date=24 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Tenerife\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_contagiati_in_italia-249569108/|title=Coronavirus, positivi due italiani a Tenerife. Mille persone nell'hotel in quarantena|date=25 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rtve.es/noticias/20200224/italiano-da-positivo-coronavirus-sur-tenerife/2004321.shtml|title=Un italiano da positivo por coronavirus en el sur de Tenerife|last=RTVE.es/AGENCIAS|date=24 February 2020|website=RTVE.es|language=es|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/25/tenerife-coronavirus-guests-hotel-quarantined|title=Tenerife coronavirus: 1,000 guests at hotel quarantined|date=25 February 2020|website=The Guardian|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 25 February, the wife of the doctor from Lombardy tested positive and was admitted to the same hospital where her husband was being treated.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://diariodeavisos.elespanol.com/2020/02/un-ciudadano-italiano-da-positivo-en-coronavirus-en-el-sur-de-tenerife/|title=Un ciudadano italiano da positivo en el sur de Tenerife por coronavirus|last=Guti\u00e9rrez|first=Juan Jes\u00fas|date=25 February 2020|website=Diario de Avisos|language=es-ES|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> A 36-year-old Italian woman living in [[Barcelona]] who had visited Bergamo and Milan from 12 to 22 February also tested positive.<ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Europe\" /><ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Tenerife\" /><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thelocal.es/20200225/woman-in-barcelona-tests-positive-to-coronavirus-the-first-confirmed-case-in-mainland-spain|title=Woman in Barcelona tests positive to coronavirus, the first confirmed case on mainland Spain|date=25 February 2020|work=thelocal.es|accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref> A man from [[Villarreal]] who had recently travelled to Milan tested positive and was admitted to Hospital Universitario de La Plana.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.levante-emv.com/comunitat-valenciana/2020/02/25/coronavirus-caso-valencia-positivo/1982275.html|title=Sanidad confirma el primer caso de coronavirus en la C. Valenciana|last=Levante-EMV|website=levante-emv.com|language=es|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> A 24-year-old man from [[Madrid]] who had recently returned from Northern Italy tested positive and was admitted to [[Hospital Carlos III]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.levante-emv.com/espana/2020/02/25/confirmado-primer-caso-coronavirus-cataluna/1982130.html|title=Un caso de coronavirus en Madrid eleva a siete los infectados en Espa\u00f1a|last=Levante-EMV|website=levante-emv.com|language=es|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telemadrid.es/noticias/madrid/Confirmado-primer-caso-coronavirus-Madrid-0-2207779217--20200225111539.html|title=Confirmado el primer caso de coronavirus en Madrid|date=25 February 2020|work=telemadrid.es|accessdate=26 February 2020|language=es}}</ref>\nOn 26 February, two Italian tourists who were vacationing with the Lombardy doctor and his wife also tested positive. The group were transferred to University Hospital of the Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Candelaria and underwent quarantine.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rtve.es/noticias/20200226/dos-nuevos-positivos-coronavirus-entre-italianos-del-hotel-adeje-canarias/2004660.shtml|title=Dos nuevos positivos por coronavirus entre los italianos del hotel de Adeje de Canarias|last=EFE|first=RTVE es /|date=26 February 2020|website=RTVE.es|language=es|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> A 22-year-old man from Barcelona who travelled to Milan between 22 and 25 February tested positive and was admitted to Hospital Cl\u00ednic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ara.cat/societat/segon-cas-coronavirus-catalunya-noi-22-anys-italia_0_2406359478.html|title=Un noi de 22 anys que havia viatjat a Mil\u00e0 \u00e9s el segon cas de coronavirus a Catalunya|last=Bassas|first=Antoni|date=26 February 2020|website=Ara.cat|language=ca-ES|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vilaweb.cat/noticies/almenys-setze-infectats-per-coronavirus-i-250-persones-en-quarantena-al-nord-ditalia/|title=[EN DIRECTE] Confirmat un segon cas de coronavirus a Catalunya|website=VilaWeb|language=ca|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> A woman from [[La Gomera]] who travelled to Italy between 4 and 8 February tested positive and was admitted to Hospital General de La Gomera in Tenerife.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.20minutos.es/noticia/4166583/0/nuevo-positivo-gomera-eleva-11-numero-infectados-coronavirus-espana/|title=Un nuevo positivo en La Gomera eleva a 11 el n\u00famero de infectados por coronavirus en Espa\u00f1a|last=20minutos|date=26 February 2020|website=20minutos.es \u2013 \u00daltimas Noticias|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 27 February, a 44-year-old man from [[Valencia]] who worked as a sportswriter and had travelled to Milan's [[San Siro]] Stadium on 19 February to watch a football game tested positive and was admitted to Hospital Cl\u00ednico [[University of Valencia|Universitario de Val\u00e8ncia]]. Two other people with whom he had made contact also tested positive and were admitted to the same hospital. Two more people who had visited the same football game in Milan were hospitalised at the same place.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Linde|first=Pablo|url=https://elpais.com/sociedad/2020/01/31/actualidad/1580509404_469734.html|title=Sanidad confirma en La Gomera el primer caso de coronavirus en Espa\u00f1a|date=1 February 2020|work=El Pa\u00eds|access-date=27 February 2020|language=es|issn=1134-6582}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.as.com/en/2020/02/27/football/1582794092_036585.html|title=Valencia fan in Milan last week for UCL tie tests positive for coronavirus|date=27 February 2020|website=AS.com|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Bono|first=Ferran|url=https://elpais.com/sociedad/2020/02/27/actualidad/1582795523_075914.html|title=Un periodista que viaj\u00f3 a Mil\u00e1n para cubrir el Valencia-Atalanta, positivo por coronavirus|date=27 February 2020|work=El Pa\u00eds|access-date=27 February 2020|language=es|issn=1134-6582}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.levante-emv.com/comunitat-valenciana/2020/02/27/coronavirus-valencia-nuevos-casos-infectados/1983062.html|title=Sanidad confirma 6 nuevos casos de coronavirus en la C. Valenciana|last=Levante-EMV|website=levante-emv.com|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> A woman who had visited Milan was hospitalised at Hospital de Sagunto, Valencia.<ref name=\":6\" /> An Italian student studying in Valencia who had visited Northern Italy was admitted to Hospital Universitario Doctor Peset.<ref name=\":6\" /> A 22-year-old woman from Tenerife who had travelled to Italy from 19 to 25 February was admitted to Hospital Cl\u00ednic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.es/espana/catalunya/abci-mujer-22-anos-viajo-italia-tercer-caso-importado-coronavirus-cataluna-202002271249_noticia.html|title=Una tinerfe\u00f1a de 22 a\u00f1os que viaj\u00f3 a Italia, tercer caso \"importado\" de coronavirus en Catalu\u00f1a|date=27 February 2020|website=abc|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> An 18-year-old Italian student studying at IE University, [[Segovia]], who had just returned from Milan, was admitted to Hospital General de Segovia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elnortedecastilla.es/segovia/ingresado-joven-habitaciones-20200227182120-nt.html|title=Un alumno italiano de IE University en Segovia, primer caso positivo de coronavirus en la regi\u00f3n|date=27 February 2020|website=El Norte de Castilla|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.leonoticias.com/castillayleon/primer-coronavirus-castilla-20200227184850-nt.html|title=Confirmados en Segovia y Valladolid los dos primeros casos registrados en Castilla y Le\u00f3n|date=27 February 2020|website=Leonoticias|language=es|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a 27-year-old man from [[Aragon]] with a history of recent trips to Milan tested positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elespanol.com/ciencia/salud/|title=Noticias sobre Salud y Medicina en EL ESPA\u00d1OL|website=El Espa\u00f1ol|language=es-ES|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Sweden''' \u2013\nOn 26 February, Sweden confirmed that a 30-year-old man who previously visited Northern Italy fell ill three days after returning to Sweden and was admitted to [[Sahlgrenska University Hospital]] in [[Gothenburg]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bolin|first=Mattias|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/lokalt/vast/bekraftat-coronafall-i-goteborg-person-vardas-pa-sahlgrenska|title=Bekr\u00e4ftat coronafall i G\u00f6teborg \u2013 person v\u00e5rdas p\u00e5 Sahlgrenska|date=26 February 2020|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=26 February 2020|language=sv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/gt/en-person-i-goteborg-har-testats-positivt-for-corona/|title=Bekr\u00e4ftat fall av Coronavirus i G\u00f6teborg \u2013 personen har varit i Italien|last=Ekstr\u00f6m|first=reas|website=Expressen|language=sv|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/nytt-bekraftat-fall-av-covid-19/|title=Nytt bekr\u00e4ftat fall av covid-19 \u2013 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 27 February, three patients in their 30s were confirmed positive in [[V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland County|V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland]]. Two of them had been in contact with the Gothenburg patient, while the other had previously visited Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/ytterligare-fall-av-covid-19-i-flera-regioner/|title=Ytterligare fall av covid-19 i flera regioner \u2013 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten|website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se|language=sv|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.cision.com/se/vastra-gotalandsregionen/r/tre-nya-bekraftade-fall-av-coronavirusinfektion--covid-19--i-vastra-gotaland,c3048641|title=Tre nya bekr\u00e4ftade fall av coronavirusinfektion (Covid-19) i V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland|website=News Powered by Cision|language=sv|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":18\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.se/20200227/five-new-cases-of-the-coronavirus-in-sweden|title=Sweden confirms five new coronavirus cases, including first patient in Stockholm|last=L\u00f6fgren|first=Emma|date=27 February 2020|website=thelocal.se|publisher=The Local|accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a man in his 50s who had returned from Northern Italy on 24 February tested positive and was admitted to a hospital in [[J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rjl.se/nyheter/nyheter-och-pressmeddelanden/pressmeddelande-28-februari-2020-ytterligare-bekraftat-fall-i-jonkopings-lan-av-nya-coronaviruset-covid-19--45553|title=Pressmeddelande 28 februari 2020: Ytterligare bekr\u00e4ftat fall i J\u00f6nk\u00f6pings l\u00e4n av nya coronaviruset (covid-19), Region J\u00f6nk\u00f6pings l\u00e4n|website=rjl.se|language=sv|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Switzerland''' \u2013\nOn 25 February, Switzerland confirmed its first case, a 70-year-old man in the canton of [[Canton of Ticino|Ticino]] who had previously visited Milan.<ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Tenerife\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-switzerland-coronavirus-idUSKBN20J1ZO|title=Swiss authorities confirm first case of coronavirus|date=25 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 27 February, a 28-year-old IT worker from [[Geneva]] who had recently returned from Milan tested positive and was admitted to [[Geneva University Hospitals|Geneva University Hospital]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/das-bag/aktuell/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78268.html|title=New coronavirus Covid-19: three new confirmed cases in Switzerland|website=bag.admin.ch|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":02\">{{cite web|url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788|title=Switzerland confirms total of four coronavirus cases|last=swissinfo.ch|first=S. W. I.|last2=Corporation|first2=a branch of the Swiss Broadcasting|website=SWI swissinfo.ch|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> Two Italian children on vacation in [[Canton of Grisons|Graub\u00fcnden]] tested positive and were hospitalised.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gr.ch/DE/institutionen/verwaltung/djsg/ga/coronavirus/Seiten/Info.aspx|title=Informationen zum Coronavirus|website=gr.ch|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":02\" /><ref name=\":92\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bielertagblatt.ch/nachrichten/schweiz/graubuenden-sagt-den-engadiner-skimarathon-ab|title=Graub\u00fcnden sagt den Engadiner Skimarathon ab|website=Bieler Tagblatt|language=de|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227174547/https://www.bielertagblatt.ch/nachrichten/schweiz/graubuenden-sagt-den-engadiner-skimarathon-ab|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> A 26-year-old man in [[Canton of Aargau|Aargau]] who had visited Verona on a business trip the previous week tested positive and was hospitalised.<ref name=\":02\" /> A 30-year-old woman who visited Milan was admitted to a hospital in [[Z\u00fcrich|Zurich]].<ref name=\":02\" /> A young woman who had travelled to Milan tested positive in [[Canton of Basel-Stadt|Basel-City]]. She worked for a daycare centre in [[Riehen]], and after her test was confirmed, the children at the daycare were put into a two-week quarantine.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-swiss-idUSKCN20L167|title=Swiss coronavirus cases rise to nine as children placed in precautionary quarantine|date=27 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref> On 28 February, her partner, a 23-year-old man, also tested positive in [[Canton of Basel-Landschaft|Basel-Country]].<ref name=\":21\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rts.ch/info/suisse/11127000-manifestations-d-ampleur-interdites-en-raison-du-coronavirus-conference-de-presse-du-conseil-federal-en-direct.html|title=Les manifestations d'ampleur interdites en Suisse en raison du coronavirus|date=28 February 2020|website=rts.ch|language=fr|access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref> On 29 February, the man's mother tested positive as well. \nOn 28 February, a 45-year-old-man who had travelled to Milan tested positive in [[Z\u00fcrich]].<ref name=\":21\" />\n\n'''Ukraine''' \u2013\nOn 3 March, Ukraine confirmed its first case in [[Chernivtsi]], a man who had travelled from Italy by plane to the Romanian city of [[Suceava]] and then to Ukraine by car with his wife.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/katyagorchinskaya/2020/03/03/first-case-of-coronavirus-registered-in-ukraine/|title=First Case Of Coronavirus Registered in Ukraine|date=3 March 2020|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''United Kingdom''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, the United Kingdom confirmed that a patient who had visited Milan tested positive and was admitted to [[Royal Free Hospital]] in London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-51656609|title=Two more coronavirus cases confirmed in England|date=27 February 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> Northern Ireland reported its first case, an adult who had travelled from Northern Italy via Dublin and was admitted to Royal Victoria Hospital in [[Belfast]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Kearney|first=Vincent|date=27 February 2020|title=NI coronavirus case had travelled through Dublin|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/health/2020/0227/1117991-ireland-coronavirus/}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, Wales reported its first case, a patient who had returned from northern Italy was treated at a specialist unit in England.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-wales-51450517|title=First case of coronavirus in Wales confirmed|date=28 February 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Oceania===\n\n'''New Zealand''' \u2013\nOn 4 March, the New Zealand Ministry of Health confirmed its second case, a woman in her 30s who returned to [[Auckland]] from Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Second Case of COVID-19 Confirmed in NZ |url=https://www.health.govt.nz/news-media/media-releases/second-case-covid-19-confirmed-nz |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Ministry of Health NZ }}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Italy|Current events|Medicine|Viruses}}\n* [[:Template:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic articles]]<!-- Template will not display if transcluded, since it causes the page to exceed the Post-expand include size -->\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in San Marino]]\n* [[Timeline of the 2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic in March 2020]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic on cruise ships]]\n* [[Pandemic]]\n* [[Epidemiology of COVID-19]]\n* [[2009 flu pandemic in Europe]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Germany]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Malta]]\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Spain]]\n* [[List of epidemics]]\n* [[Coronavirus disease 2019]]\n* [[Coronavirus disease]]s, a group of closely related syndromes\n* [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]]\n* [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome-related coronavirus]]\n* [[Contact tracing]], inquiry opened immediately to identify and contact everyone who has been in close contact with an infected person and subsequent collection of further information about these contacts\n\n==References==\n<references /><!-- Do not replace with {{reflist}}, since that would hide references if the Post-expand include size of the page is exceeded -->\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite web |url = http://www.salute.gov.it/nuovocoronavirus |publisher=[[Ministry of Health (Italy)|Ministero della Salute]] |title=Official website|language=italian}}\n* {{cite web | url = http://opendatadpc.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/b0c68bce2cce478eaac82fe38d4138b1 | title = Geomap and open data on the diffusion of COVID-19 in Italy | website = [[Protezione Civile]] | archive-url = http://archive.is/wip/fViDD | archive-date = 12 March 2020 | url-status = live}} (desktop version)\n* {{cite web |url=https://coronavirus-global.com/italy |title=Coronavirus Italy updates and news |trans-title=Latest news and statistics of coronavirus in Italy. |access-date=4 April 2020 |language=English, French, Spanish, Portuguese, German, Italian, Swedish, Norwegian, Finnish, Estonian, Russian}}\n* [http://italy.coronamapper.com Map of the virus in Italy]\n* {{cite web |publisher=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|title=Coronavirus in Italia |url =https://lab24.ilsole24ore.com/coronavirus/|language=italian}}\n* {{cite web |first=Emanuele|last= Degani |title=Monitoring COVID-19 evolution in Italy|url =https://achab94.shinyapps.io/covid-19/}}\n* [https://corona.arrangy.com Corona Arrangy] \u2013 Map the coronavirus global statistics and route paths of confirmed cases\n\n{{COVID-19|short=true}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Italy]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy| ]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Italy]]\n[[Category:2020 in Italy]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Italy]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Ongoing viral pandemic in Italy}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy\n| map1            = COVID-19 outbreak Italy per capita cases map.svg\n| legend1         = Confirmed cases per million residents by province<br>(as of 16 April 2020).\n| map2            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Italy (Density).svg\n| legend2         = Number of confirmed cases by province<br>(as of 20 April 2020). \n{{legend|#FCEED3|50\u201399 confirmed}}\n{{legend|#F2A88D|100\u2013499 confirmed}}{{legend|#E36654|500\u2013999 confirmed}}{{legend|#E5354B|1,000\u20134,999 confirmed}}{{legend|#87353F|5,000\u20139,999 confirmed}}{{legend|#630606|\u226510,000 confirmed}}\n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = Italy\n| first_case      = \n| arrival_date    = 31 January 2020<br/>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=01|day1=31|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| first_outbreak  = [[Wuhan]], Hubei, China\n| index_case      = Rome\n| confirmed_cases = 189,973<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\"/>\n| active_cases    = 106,848<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\"/>\n| suspected_cases = \n| severe_cases    = \n| critical_cases  = 2,267<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\"/>\n| ventilator_cases = \n| recovery_cases  = 57,576<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\"/> {{small|(incl. discharged)}}\n| deaths          = 25,549<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\"/>\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|www.salute.gov.it/nuovocoronavirus}}\n}}\n\nAn [[2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic|ongoing pandemic]] of [[coronavirus disease 2019]] ({{nowrap|COVID-19}}), a novel infectious disease caused by [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus&nbsp;2]] ({{nowrap|SARS-CoV-2}}), was first confirmed to have spread to Italy on 31 January 2020, when two Chinese tourists in Rome tested positive for the virus.<ref name=\"Corriere_20Jan\">{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Primi due casi in Italia|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_gennaio_30/coronavirus-italia-corona-9d6dc436-4343-11ea-bdc8-faf1f56f19b7.shtml |website=Corriere della sera |accessdate=31 January 2020 |date=31 January 2020|language=it}}</ref> One week later an Italian man repatriated back to Italy from the city of [[Wuhan]], China, was hospitalised and confirmed as the third case in Italy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-italy-idUSKBN20F0UI|title=First Italian dies of coronavirus as outbreak flares in north|date=21 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> A cluster of cases was later detected, starting with 16 confirmed cases in [[Lombardy]] on 21 February,<ref name=\"ThomReut_IT_16cluster_21Feb\">{{cite news | last1= Anzolin | first1= Elisa | last2= Amante | first2= Angelo | title= Coronavirus outbreak grows in northern Italy, 16 cases reported in one day | date=21 February 2020 | agency=[[Thomson Reuters]] | url= https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-italy/coronavirus-outbreak-grows-in-northern-italy-16-cases-reported-in-one-day-idUSKBN20F0UI |accessdate=21 February 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200221225322/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-italy/coronavirus-outbreak-grows-in-northern-italy-16-cases-reported-in-one-day-idUSKBN20F0UI |archivedate= 21 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> and 60 additional cases and the first deaths on 22 February.<ref name=\"CorrieredSera_76_recent_cases\" /> By the beginning of March, the virus had spread to all regions of Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus. Colpite tutte le regioni. La Protezione civile: ecco i numeri aggiornati |url=https://www.avvenire.it/attualita/pagine/coronavirus-aggiornamento-5-marzo-2020 |accessdate=19 March 2020 |work=Avvenire |date=5 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 January, the Italian government suspended all flights to and from China and declared a state of emergency. In February, eleven municipalities in [[northern Italy]] were identified as the centres of the two main Italian clusters and placed under quarantine. The majority of positive cases in other regions traced back to these two clusters.<ref name=\":8\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_in_italia_aggiornamento_ora_per_ora-249241616/|title=Coronavirus in Italia: aggiornamento ora per ora|date=22 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> On 8 March 2020, Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] expanded the quarantine to all of Lombardy and 14 other northern provinces, and on the following day to all of Italy, [[2020 Italy coronavirus lockdown|placing more than 60 million people in quarantine]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Northern Italy quarantines 16 million people |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238 |website=BBC |accessdate=8 March 2020 |date=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news |title=All of Italy to be placed on coronavirus lockdown |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51810673 |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=BBC News |date=9 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-italy-sees-largest-daily-rise-in-deaths-and-confirmed-cases-11953192|title=Coronavirus: Italy deaths jump to 463, with 300 in just one region|publisher=Sky News|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref> On 11 March 2020, Conte prohibited nearly all commercial activity except for supermarkets and pharmacies.<ref name=\":12\">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/merkel-coronavirus-germany/2020/03/11/e276252a-6399-11ea-8a8e-5c5336b32760_story.html|title=Italy ramps up coronavirus lockdown, Merkel warns virus could infect two-thirds of Germany|last=Harlan|first=Chico|last2=Morris|first2=Loveday|website=The Washington Post|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":13\">{{Cite news|last=Rome|first=Eric Sylvers in Milan and Giovanni Legorano in|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/italy-hardens-nationwide-quarantine-11583962093|title=Italy Hardens Nationwide Quarantine|date=12 March 2020|work=The Wall Street Journal|access-date=12 March 2020|issn=0099-9660}}</ref> On 21 March, the Italian government closed all non-essential businesses and industries, and restricted movement of people.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Safi |first1=Michael |last2=Giuffrida |first2=Angela |last3=Farrer |first3=Martin |title=Coronavirus: Italy bans any movement inside country as toll nears 5,500 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/italian-pm-warns-of-worst-crisis-since-ww2-as-coronavirus-deaths-leap-by-almost-800 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 March 2020, the Italian College of Anesthesia, Analgesia, Resuscitation and Intensive Care (SIAARTI) published [[medical ethics]] recommendations regarding [[triage]] protocols that might need to be employed.<ref>{{cite techreport|url=http://www.siaarti.it/SiteAssets/News/COVID19%20-%20documenti%20SIAARTI/SIAARTI%20-%20Covid19%20-%20Raccomandazioni%20di%20etica%20clinica.pdf|title=Raccomandazioni di etica clinica per l\u2019ammissione a trattamenti intensivi e per la loro sospensione, in condizioni eccezionali di squilibrio tra necessit\u00e0 e risorse disponibili|institution=Italian College of Anesthesia, Analgesia, Resuscitation and Intensive Care (SIAARTI)|language=it|date=6 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|url-status=live|format=PDF|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312202813/http://www.siaarti.it/SiteAssets/News/COVID19%20-%20documenti%20SIAARTI/SIAARTI%20-%20Covid19%20-%20Raccomandazioni%20di%20etica%20clinica.pdf|archive-date=12 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/who-gets-hospital-bed/607807/|title=The Extraordinary Decisions Facing Italian Doctors|last=Mounk|first=Yascha|date=11 March 2020|work=[[The Atlantic]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233745/https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/who-gets-hospital-bed/607807/|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|quote=Now the Italian College of Anesthesia, Analgesia, Resuscitation and Intensive Care (SIAARTI) has published guidelines for the criteria that doctors and nurses should follow in these extraordinary circumstances. The document begins by likening the moral choices facing Italian doctors to the forms of wartime triage that are required in the field of \"catastrophe medicine.\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-italy-doctors-tough-calls-survival/|title=Italian doctors on coronavirus frontline face tough calls on whom to save|last=Privitera|first=Greta|date=11 March 2020|work=[[Politico]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312125640/https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-italy-doctors-tough-calls-survival/|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|quote=\u2026the Italian Society of Anesthesia, Analgesia, Resuscitation and Intensive Care, who co-authored new guidelines on how to prioritize treatment of coronavirus cases in hospitals\u2026}}</ref>\n\n{{As of|2020|04|23}}, Italy is one of the world's centres of active coronavirus cases with 106,848 active cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6|title=Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases by the Center for Systems Science and Engineering (CSSE) at Johns Hopkins |access-date=25 March 2020}}</ref> The total of confirmed cases is 189,973, with 25,549 deaths, and 57,576 recoveries or dismissals.<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\">{{cite web|url=http://www.salute.gov.it/portale/nuovocoronavirus/dettaglioContenutiNuovoCoronavirus.jsp?lingua=italiano&id=5351&area=nuovoCoronavirus&menu=vuoto|title=Covid-19 \u2013 Situazione in Italia|website=salute.gov.it|publisher=Ministero della Salute|language=it|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref> By 23 April, Italy had conducted about 1,580,000 tests for the virus, and tested about 1,052,000 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salute.gov.it/imgs/C_17_notizie_4583_0_file.pdf |title=AGGIORNAMENTO 23/04/2020 ORE 17.00 |date=23 April 2020 |url-status=live |access-date=24 March 2020}}</ref> Due to the limited number of tests performed, the real number of infected people in Italy, as in other countries, is estimated to be higher than the official count.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Flaxman |first1=Seth |last2=Swapnil |first2=Mishra |last3=Gandy |first3=Axel |display-authors=etal |title=Report 13: Estimating the number of infections and the impact of non-pharmaceutical interventions on COVID-19 in 11 European countries |date=30 March 2020 |pages=1\u201335 |doi=10.25561/77731 |url=https://spiral.imperial.ac.uk:8443/handle/10044/1/77731 |accessdate=31 March 2020 |publisher=Imperial College London}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last=Lau |first=Hien |last2=Khosrawipour |first2=Veria |last3=Kocbach |first3=Piotr |last4=Mikolajczyk |first4=Agata |last5=Ichii |first5=Hirohito |last6=Schubert |first6=Justyna |last7=Bania |first7=Jacek |last8=Khosrawipour |first8=Tanja |date=14 March 2020 |title=Internationally lost COVID-19 cases |url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1684118220300736 |journal=Journal of Microbiology, Immunology and Infection  |doi=10.1016/j.jmii.2020.03.013 |pmid=32205091 |pmc=7102572 |issn=1684-1182}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=The total number of Italian coronavirus cases could be '10 times higher' than known tally, according to one official |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/24/italian-coronavirus-cases-seen-10-times-higher-than-official-tally.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |publisher=CNBC |date=24 March 2020 }}</ref> On 19 March, Italy became the country with the highest number of confirmed coronavirus deaths in the world, but on 11 April it was overtaken by the United States.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2020/03/19/coronavirus-italy-now-has-more-covid-19-deaths-than-china/2873835001/|title=Grim milestone: Italy's coronavirus deaths surpass China's|first=Eric J. Lyman and Kim|last=Hjelmgaard|website=USA Today}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: US overtakes Italy as country with most deaths |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/11/us-coronavirus-death-toll |accessdate=12 April 2020 |publisher=The Guardian |date=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nOn 31 December 2019, the Health Commission of [[Wuhan]], Hubei, China, informed the [[World Health Organization|WHO]] about a cluster of acute pneumonia cases with unknown origin in its province. On 9 January 2020, the [[Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention]] (CCDC) reported the identification of a [[novel coronavirus]] (later identified as the [[SARS-CoV-2]]) as the cause.<ref>{{cite web |title=Covid-19 \u2013 Situazione nel mondo |url=http://www.salute.gov.it/portale/nuovocoronavirus/dettaglioContenutiNuovoCoronavirus.jsp?lingua=italiano&id=5338&area=nuovoCoronavirus&menu=vuoto |website=salute.gov.it |accessdate=4 March 2020 |language=IT}}</ref> In late January 2020, following the [[Mainland China during the 2019\u20132020 coronavirus outbreak|developments of COVID-19 outbreak in mainland China]], on 3 February, Italy set up enhanced screening measures, including thermal cameras and medical staff at airports.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Timeline==\n{{Update section |date=March 2020}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Italy medical cases chart}}\n\n===First confirmed cases===\nOn 31 January, the first two cases of COVID-19 were confirmed in Rome. A Chinese couple, originally from Wuhan, who had arrived in Italy on 23 January via [[Milan Malpensa Airport]], travelled from the airport to [[Verona]], then to Parma, arriving in Rome on 28 January. The next afternoon, they developed a cough, and by evening the man had a fever; the couple were taken to the [[Lazzaro Spallanzani National Institute for Infectious Diseases]] where they tested positive for SARS-CoV-2 and were hospitalised.<ref name=\"prima\">{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_gennaio_31/virus-primi-due-casi-italia-due-cinesi-marito-moglie-italia-dieci-giorni-e365df1c-43b3-11ea-bdc8-faf1f56f19b7.shtml|title=Prima a Milano, poi l'hotel a Roma: le tappe dei 7 giorni di viaggio della coppia contagiata|last=Frignani|first=Rinaldo|date=31 January 2020|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Corriere_20Jan\"/> On 2 February, a team from the same institute composed of scientists Maria Rosaria Capobianchi, Francesca Colavita, and Concetta Castilletti isolated the genomic sequence of the virus and uploaded it to [[GenBank]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Armstrong |first1=Mark |title=Italian scientists isolate DNA sequence of coronavirus |url=https://www.euronews.com/2020/02/02/italian-scientists-isolate-dna-sequence-of-coronavirus |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=euronews |date=2 February 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://tg24.sky.it/cronaca/photogallery/2020/02/02/coronavirus-italia-spallanzani-roma.html |work=[[Sky TG24]]|accessdate=2 February 2020|language=italian|title=Le tre ricercatrici che hanno isolato il Coronavirus allo Spallanzani di Roma.}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 January, the Italian government suspended all flights to and from China and declared a state of emergency with the duration of six months. Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] said Italy was the first EU country to take this kind of precautionary measure.<ref name=\"thelocal-flight\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.it/20200131/italy-suspends-all-china-flights-after-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-in-rome/|title=Italy suspends all China flights as coronavirus cases confirmed in Rome|date=31 January 2020|website=THELOCAL|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref> The government also introduced thermal scanners and temperature checks on international passengers arriving at Italian airports.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_04/coronavirus-controlli-gli-scanner-termici-aeroporti-italiani-c10b73d2-4796-11ea-bec1-6ac729c309c6.shtml|title=Coronavirus, controlli con gli scanner termici negli aeroporti italiani|last=Berberi|first=Leonard|date=2 April 2020|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 February, an Italian repatriated from Wuhan tested positive for COVID-19, bringing the total number of cases in Italy to three.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-06-20-intl-hnk/index.html|title=February 6 coronavirus news|first1=Jessie |last1=Yeung |first2=Adam |last2=Renton |first3=Steve|last3=George|date=6 February 2020|publisher=CNN}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 February, the repatriated Italian recovered and was discharged from the hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.open.online/2020/02/22/coronavirus-bollettino-dello-spallanzani-guarito-il-ricercatore-italiano-verra-dimesso-oggi/|title=Coronavirus, bollettino dello Spallanzani: guarito il ricercatore italiano, verr\u00e0 dimesso oggi. Niccol\u00f2 \"sta benissimo\" \u2013 Il video|date=22 February 2020|website=Open|language=it-IT|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> On 22 and 26 February, the two previously infected Chinese tourists tested negative for COVID-19 at Lazzaro Spallanzani National Institute in Rome.<ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/mondo/coronavirus_diretta_morti_contagi_oggi_ultime_notizie_26_febbraio_2020-5075865.html|title=Coronavirus, diretta. Contagi a quota 424, primo caso in Puglia, 12 morti. Lombardia, Fontana \u00e8 negativo, ma resta in isolamento per 14 giorni|website=Il Messaggero}}</ref>\n\n===Clusters in northern Italy===\n====Lombardy====\nThe [[Lombardy]] outbreak came to light when a 38-year-old Italian tested positive in [[Codogno]], a [[comune]] in the [[province of Lodi]]. On 14 February, he felt unwell and went to a doctor in [[Castiglione d'Adda]]. He was prescribed treatments for influenza.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /> On 16 February, as the man's condition worsened, he went to Codogno Hospital, reporting respiratory problems.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\">{{Cite news |title=Codogno, i medici dell'ospedale in trincea: \"Quelle accuse del premier fanno pi\u00f9 male della malattia\"|language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=26 February 2020 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/codogno_i_medici_dell_ospedale_in_trincea_quelle_accuse_del_premier_fanno_piu_male_della_malattia_-249593374/ |accessdate=26 February 2020}}</ref> Initially there was no suspicion of COVID-19, so no additional precautionary measures were taken, and the virus was able to infect other patients and health workers.<ref name=\"urlMailand:NZZ\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nzz.ch/international/mailand-coronavirus-epidemie-begann-in-spital-ld.1542330 |title=Mailand: Coronavirus-Epidemie begann in Spital |accessdate=24 February 2020 |website= nzz.ch (Neue Zurcher Zeitung)}}</ref> On 19 February, the wife of the patient revealed he had met an Italian friend who had returned from China on 21 January, who subsequently tested negative.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /> Later, the patient, his pregnant wife and a friend tested positive.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /> On 20 February, three more cases were confirmed after the patients reported symptoms of [[pneumonia]].<ref name=\":1\">{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, primi tre contagi in Italia: 38enne, sua moglie e un amico in terapia intensiva. La donna insegna in un liceo |language=Italian |publisher=La Repubblica |url= https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/21/news/coronavirus_a_milano_contaggiato_38enne_e_un_italiano_ricoverato_a_codogno-249121707/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I249146878-C12-P1-S1.12-T1 |accessdate=21 February 2020 |date=21 February 2020}}</ref> Thereafter, extensive screenings and checks were performed on everyone that had possibly been in contact with or near the infected subjects.<ref name=\"Messaggero_22Feb\">{{cite news |url= https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_diretta_lombardia_codogno_italiano_ultime_notizie-5064423.html |title=Coronavirus, diretta: morto uomo di 78 anni a Padova, \u00e8 la prima vittima italiana |website=Il Messaggero |date=22 February 2020 |accessdate=22 February 2020 |language=Italian}}</ref> It has been subsequently reported that the origin of these cases has a possible connection to the first European local transmission that occurred in [[Munich]], Germany, on 19 January 2020, consistent with phylogenetic analysis of viral genome.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Munich_Codogno\">{{cite news |last1=Luna |first1=Riccardo |title=Coronavirus: il paziente tedesco |url=https://rep.repubblica.it/pwa/generale/2020/03/05/news/coronavirus-250377117/ |accessdate=11 March 2020 |work=La Repubblica |date=5 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref><ref name=\"nextstrain\">{{cite web|url=https://nextstrain.org/ncov?dmax=2020-03-08&dmin=2019-12-15&fbclid=IwAR3UreH6NMoS8IjQqWOJpYdTX_Ygc5bW4gcBBf2gWe_QTDwxIL0oLMuwSgY|title=Genomic epidemiology of novel coronavirus (hCoV-19)| website=nextstrain.org|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=pmid32003551>{{cite journal |last1=Rothe |first1=Camilla |last2=Schunk |first2=Mirjam |last3=Sothmann |first3=Peter |last4=Bretzel |first4=Gisela |last5=Froeschl |first5=Guenter |last6=Wallrauch |first6=Claudia |last7=Zimmer |first7=Thorbj\u00f6rn |last8=Thiel |first8=Verena |last9=Janke |first9=Christian |last10=Guggemos |first10=Wolfgang |last11=Seilmaier |first11=Michael |last12=Drosten |first12=Christian  |author-link12=Christian Drosten |last13=Vollmar |first13=Patrick |last14=Zwirglmaier |first14=Katrin |last15=Zange |first15=Sabine |last16=W\u00f6lfel |first16=Roman |last17=Hoelscher |first17=Michael |title=Transmission of 2019-nCoV Infection from an Asymptomatic Contact in Germany |journal=New England Journal of Medicine |date=5 March 2020 |volume=382 |issue=10 |pages=970\u2013971 |doi=10.1056/NEJMc2001468 |pmid=32003551 |pmc=7120970 }}</ref> The 38-year-old man was asymptomatic for weeks, reportedly led an active social life and potentially interacted with dozens of people before spreading the virus at Codogno Hospital.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /><ref name=\"urlMailand:NZZ\" /> Afterward, he was transferred to [[Policlinico San Matteo]] in [[Pavia]],<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/italia/13566825/coronavirus-paziente-uno-codogno-trasferimento-pavia.html |title=Coronavirus, il 38enne paziente uno di Codogno trasferito nella notte a Pavia |website=liberoquotidiano.it |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref> and his wife to [[Ospedale Luigi Sacco|Sacco Hospital]] in Milan.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://edition.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-25-20-hnk-intl/h_485832164169510b66e7bb07479c75b0 |title=Italian authorities identify first known patient to have caught coronavirus in Lombardy |first1=Helen |last1=Regan |first2=Adam |last2=Renton |date=25 February 2020 |publisher=CNN |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url= https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_paziente_1_ancora_grave_ma_stazionario_la_moglie_incinta_sta_bene-249550115/ |title=Coronavirus, \"paziente 1\" ancora grave ma stazionario, la moglie incinta sta bene |language=Italian |date=25 February 2020 |work=la Repubblica |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Emergenza coronavirus (49496308758).jpg|thumb|upright=1.13|[[Protezione Civile|Civil Protection]] volunteers carrying out health checks at [[Guglielmo Marconi Airport]]]]\nOn 21 February 16 more cases were confirmed \u2013 14 in Lombardy, including the doctor who prescribed treatments to the 38-year-old Codogno man,<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /> and two in [[Veneto]]. On 22 February, a 77-year-old woman from [[Casalpusterlengo]], who suffered from pneumonia and visited the same emergency room as the 38-year-old from Codogno, died in Lombardy.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/lombardia/coronavirus-morta-una-donna-in-lombardia-seconda-vittima-italiana_15150431-202002a.shtml|title=Coronavirus, morta una donna in Lombardia: seconda vittima italiana |website=Tgcom24 |language=Italian |accessdate=22 February 2020}}</ref> Including the 78-year-old man who died in Veneto, the number of cases in Italy rose to 79.<ref name=\"CorrieredSera_76_recent_cases\" /><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, in Veneto la prima vittima, Adriano Trevisan, 78 anni. Venti contagiati in Italia. Conte: \"Nuove misure\" |date=22 February 2020 |work=la Repubblica |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/cina_coronavirus_italia_virus_wuhan_influenza_codogno_lombardia_veneto_adriano_trevisan-249215365/}}</ref> Of the 76 newly discovered cases, 54 were found in Lombardy, including one patient in [[San Raffaele Hospital]] in Milan<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml |title=Coronavirus, due casi a Milano |first=Simona |last=Ravizza |date=22 February 2020 |website=Corriere della Sera |language=Italian |accessdate=23 February 2020}}</ref> and eight patients in [[Policlinico San Matteo]] in [[Pavia]],<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, a Pavia 8 pazienti ricoverati al San Matteo: anche una coppia di medici |language=Italian |website=Il Messaggero |date=22 February 2020 |url= https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_pavia_medici_contagiati_pieve_porto_morone_chignolo_po_cosa_sta_succedendo_22_febbraio_2020-5068178.html |accessdate=23 February 2020}}</ref> 17 in Veneto, two in [[Emilia-Romagna]], two in [[Lazio]] and one in [[Piedmont]].<ref>{{Cite news |first=Simona |last=Ravizza |title=Coronavirus, due casi a Milano |date=22 February 2020 |language=Italian |website=Corriere della Sera |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml |accessdate=22 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 February, a 68-year-old woman with cancer from [[Trescore Cremasco]] died in [[Crema, Lombardy|Crema]]. The number of cases in Italy rose to 152, including fourteen patients being treated at Policlinico San Matteo in Pavia.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/23/news/coronavirus_italia-249329434/ |title=Coronavirus, terza vittima in Italia: \u00e8 una donna ricoverata a Crema. 152 casi positivi |date=23 February 2020 |website=la Repubblica |language=Italian |access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.globalist.it/news/2020/02/23/coronavirus-sale-a-14-il-numero-dei-casi-ricoverati-a-pavia-2053548.html |title=Coronavirus, sale a 14 il numero dei casi ricoverati a Pavia |publisher=globalist.it |language=Italian |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref> On 24 February, an 84-year-old man with pre-existing medical conditions from [[Villa di Serio]] died in [[Bergamo]] while hospitalised in the Papa Giovanni XXIII Hospital.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/quarto-morto-in-italia-per-il-coronavirus-aveva-84-anni_it_5e5381b7c5b6b82aa65555f4 |title=Quarto morto in Italia per il coronavirus, aveva 84 anni |date=24 February 2020 |website=L'HuffPost |language=Italian |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref> An 88-year-old man from [[Caselle Landi]], who resided in Codogno, died on the same day.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/coronavirus-quarta-vittima-a-bergamo-in-lombardia-scoperti-150-casi_15242453-202002a.shtml |title=Coronavirus, in Italia si contano sei vittime e 230 contagi &#124; In Lombardia il numero maggiore dei casi |website=Tgcom24}}</ref><ref name=\"Repubblica_24Jan\" /> An 80-year-old man from [[Castiglione d\u2019Adda]] died at the Luigi Sacco Hospital in Milan. He was previously hospitalised in Lodi because of a heart attack, and then transferred to Milan when confirmed as positive.<ref name=\"Repubblica_24Jan\">{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, sei morti in Italia, 229 contagi. Le vittime di oggi hanno tutte pi\u00f9 di 80 anni |language=Italian |website=la Repubblica |date=24 February 2020 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_149_i_casi_confermati_conte_i_contagi_possono_crescere_-249427098/ |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.ansa.it/canale_saluteebenessere/notizie/sanita/2020/02/24/coronavirus-_60aae600-8535-44d9-86de-48c4b71478ef.html |title=Coronavirus: sesta vittima in Italia, morto 80enne a Milano. Smentita dalla Regione Lombardia la morte della donna a Brescia \u2013 Salute & Benessere |date=22 February 2020 |website=ANSA.it}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_24/coronavirus-chi-sono-vittime-italia-74e27360-56f6-11ea-b89d-a5ca249e9e1e.shtml |title=L'ex muratore , gli anziani ricoverati: chi sono le vittime |last=Del Frate |first=Claudio |date=24 February 2020 |website=Corriere della Sera |language=Italian |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref> A 62-year-old man with pre-existing medical conditions from Castiglione d'Adda died in [[Ospedale Sant'Anna|Sant'Anna Hospital]] in [[Como]].<ref>{{cite web |location=Italy |url= https://www.fanpage.it/attualita/corona-la-settima-vittima-e-un-62enne-di-castiglione-dadda-era-ricoverato-allospedale-di-como/ |title=Coronavirus, c'\u00e8 la settima vittima italiana: un 62enne di Castiglione d'Adda, era ricoverato a Como |website=Fanpage}}</ref> Lombardy governor [[Attilio Fontana]] announced that the number of cases in Lombardy had risen to 172, with a total of 229 confirmed in Italy.<ref name=\"Corriere_24Feb\">{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_24/coronavirus-italia-ultime-notizie-oggi-nord-23035e06-56ce-11ea-b89d-a5ca249e9e1e.shtml|title=Coronavirus in Italia, i contagi sono pi\u00f9 di 200: gli ultimi aggiornamenti|last=Online|first=Chiara Severgnini e Redazione|date=24 February 2020|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, quarto morto, \u00e8 un 84enne di Bergamo. |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=24 February 2020 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_149_i_casi_confermati_conte_i_contagi_possono_crescere_-249427098/ |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, sette morti in Italia, 229 contagi |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=24 February 2020 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_149_i_casi_confermati_conte_i_contagi_possono_crescere_-249427098/ |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref> On 25 February, an 84-year-old man from [[Nembro]], a 91-year-old man from [[San Fiorano]] and an 83-year-old woman from Codogno died from complications caused by the infections.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Del Frate |first=Claudio |title=L'ex muratore , gli anziani ricoverati: chi sono le vittime |language=Italian |work=Corriere della Sera |date=24 February 2020 |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_24/coronavirus-chi-sono-vittime-italia-74e27360-56f6-11ea-b89d-a5ca249e9e1e.shtml |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus in Lombardia, salgono a 206 le persone contagiate |language=Italian |work=la Repubblica |date=25 February 2020 |url= https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_in_lombardia_salgono_a_206_le_persone_contagiate-249527654/ |accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_count\">{{Cite news |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_toscana-249520102/ |title=Coronavirus, 325 casi in Italia. Altri tre morti in Lombardia e uno in Veneto, le vittime diventano 11 |date=25 February 2020 |work=la Repubblica |language=Italian |access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe number of cases in Emilia-Romagna rose to 23, spreading through the provinces of [[Province of Piacenza|Piacenza]], [[Province of Parma|Parma]], [[Province of Modena|Modena]] and [[Province of Rimini|Rimini]]. These were all linked to the Lombardy cluster.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https:/