 Italy is the source of most of its cases.\n\n'''Belarus''' \u2013\nA case was confirmed as having been imported from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://belsat.eu/en/news/six-coronavirus-cases-in-belarus-ministry/|title=Six coronavirus cases in Belarus \u2013 ministry|website=belsat.eu|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aysor.am/en/news/2020/03/04/belarus-coronavirus/1666615|title=Six coronavirus cases confirmed in Belarus \u2013 aysor.am \u2013 Hot news from Armenia|first=Helix Consulting|last=LLC|website=aysor.am|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Bosnia and Herzegovina''' \u2013\nA man working in Italy transmitted the virus to his child.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://balkaninsight.com/2020/03/05/bosnia-confirms-two-coronavirus-cases-expects-more/|title=Bosnia Confirms Two Coronavirus Cases, Expects More|date=5 March 2020|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Croatia''' \u2013\nOn 25 February, Croatia confirmed its first case, a 26-year-old man who had stayed in Milan between 19 and 21 February and was hospitalised at the Dr. Fran Mihaljevi\u0107 University Hospital for Infectious Diseases in [[Zagreb]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Newey|first=Sarah|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/global-health/science-and-disease/coronavirus-news-uk-italy-china-south-korea-pandemic/|title=Coronavirus latest news: Britons returning from Italy told to self-isolate as Matt Hancock says he is 'worried'|date=25 February 2020|work=The Telegraph|access-date=25 February 2020|last2=Kelly-Linden|first2=Jordan|issn=0307-1235|last3=Team|first3=Global Health Security}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2160148|title=U Rijeci potvr\u0111en tre\u0107i slu\u010daj koronavirusa u Hrvatskoj|website=index.hr|language=hr|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 26 February, the man's twin brother tested positive and was admitted to the same hospital. A Croatian man who worked in [[Parma]], Italy also tested positive and was admitted to a hos