12 March 2020|via=bbc.com}}</ref>\n\n'''Slovakia''' \u2013\nAn asymptomatic man who had travelled to Venice between 14 and 15 February transmitted the virus to his father and his wife.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://spectator.sme.sk/c/22352401/three-coronavirus-cases-in-slovakia.html|title=Three coronavirus cases confirmed in Slovakia|first=Petit Press|last=a.s|date=7 March 2020|website=spectator.sme.sk|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Slovenia''' \u2013\nMany Slovenian cases are linked to Italy, including the nation's first case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.24ur.com/novice/slovenija/epidemiologi-iscejo-vse-s-katerimi-je-imel-okuzeni-slovenec-stike.html|title=Oku\u017ebo s koronavirusom potrdili \u017ee pri \u0161estih osebah, ne gre samo za motoriste iz Maroka|website=24ur.com|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Spain''' \u2013\nOn 24 February, a 69-year-old medical doctor from Lombardy who had been vacationing in [[Tenerife]] since 17 February tested positive at the [[Hospital Universitario Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Candelaria|University Hospital of the Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Candelaria]]. A 25-year-old man returning from a holiday in Italy also tested positive in [[Asturias]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_italiano_positivo_al_test_a_tenerife_e_il_terzo_caso_di_contagio_in_spagna-249508945/|title=Turista italiano positivo al test a Tenerife. Primo caso sospetto nelle Asturie: \u00e8 un giovane di ritorno dall'Italia|date=24 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Tenerife\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_contagiati_in_italia-249569108/|title=Coronavirus, positivi due italiani a Tenerife. Mille persone nell'hotel in quarantena|date=25 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rtve.es/noticias/20200224/italiano-da-positivo-